    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nImprove handling of the bothersome `Unknown filetype` healthcheck warnings most commonly seen on slightly unusual filetypes registered by valid LSP configs, built-in registry-only filetypes like `beancount` and user-defined entries added with `vim.filetype.add()`.\r\n\r\nLimitations discussed in #38082 and #38081 (namely this *not* fixing the lack of a single exhaustive filetype list), and enabled by #38831.\r\n\r\nFixes #38082.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nCombine the following two sources available here:\r\n\r\n- `getcompletion('', 'filetype')` (keep the original approach)\r\n- `vim.filetype.inspect()` (also include these filetype names)\r\n\r\nI also added two tests:\r\n\r\n1. no warning for the built-in registry-only filetype `beancount`\r\n2. no warning for a custom `mdx` filetype added via `vim.filetype.add()`\r\n\r\nFor example, the filetype `hbs` still warns, so extension names are not treated as valid filetypes.\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-08T16:30:35Z",
